## Optimization Summary - Q22 Iteration 9

### **Bottleneck Identified**
The previous iteration (367.85ms) was dominated by:
- **Dictionary loading: 179.34ms (48%)** - Loading all 1.5M phone strings from the dictionary file into std::vector<std::string> via repeated std::getline() calls
- **Filter & aggregate: 176.27ms (48%)** - The main scan and filtering

### **Root Cause Analysis (Level 0 Anti-Pattern)**
The code was using the anti-pattern of loading an entire large dictionary into memory as std::vector<std::string>:
```cpp
std::vector<std::string> load_dictionary(const std::string& dict_file) {
    std::vector<std::string> dict;
    std::ifstream f(dict_file);
    std::string line;
    while (std::getline(f, line)) {
        dict.push_back(line);  // 1.5M strings in memory!
    }
    return dict;
}
```

Then iterating through all 1.5M entries to build the set of target codes, even though we only care about 7 countries.

### **Optimization Applied**
**Streaming Dictionary Decode**: Instead of loading the entire dictionary into memory, stream through the file once and store ONLY the phone codes and countries that match our target set:

```cpp
std::unordered_map<int32_t, std::string> build_phone_code_to_country(
    const std::string& dict_file,
    const std::unordered_set<std::string>& target_countries) {
    std::unordered_map<int32_t, std::string> phone_code_to_country;
    std::ifstream f(dict_file);
    std::string line;
    int32_t code = 0;

    while (std::getline(f, line)) {
        // Only check first 2 chars (country code is always at position 0-1)
        if (line.length() >= 2 && line[2] == '-') {
            std::string country = line.substr(0, 2);
            if (target_countries.count(country)) {
                phone_code_to_country[code] = country;  // Store ONLY matching codes
            }
        }
        code++;
    }
    return phone_code_to_country;
}
```

### **Expected Impact**
- **Dict load**: 179ms → ~5-10ms (90% reduction)
  - File I/O still required, but no large in-memory allocation
  - Only storing 7 country mappings instead of 1.5M strings
  
- **Total**: 367.85ms → **~280-290ms** (estimated 23% improvement)
  - Keeps all other optimizations from previous iterations (pre-built hash index, parallel aggregation, etc.)

### **Code Preservation**
✅ All [TIMING] lines preserved inside #ifdef GENDB_PROFILE guards  
✅ Encoding logic unchanged  
✅ CSV output format preserved (comma-delimited)  
✅ Correctness maintained (only optimized dictionary loading approach)  

